#System Architecture
User Input
↓
Graphical User Interface
↓
Command Processing Engine
↓
Response Generation Module
↓
Text-to-Speech Engine
↓
User Output
  #Modules
  #GUI Module
  The GUI Module provides the visual interface through which users interact with JarvisAI.
  Built using Tkinter, it includes the chat area, input field, control buttons, system monitor, weather panel, clock, and status indicators.
    It enables both text-based interaction and easy access to the assistant's features.
    #Voice Recognition Module
    The Voice Recognition Module allows JarvisAI to understand spoken commands.
    Using the SpeechRecognition library and Google Speech Recognition API.
    It captures audio from the microphone, converts speech into text, and forwards the recognized command to the assistant for processing.
    #Text-To-Speech(TTS) Module
      The Text-to-Speech Module enables JarvisAI to communicate verbally with the user.
      It uses Edge TTS to convert generated text responses into natural-sounding speech and plays the audio back to the user, creating a more interactive and human-like experience.
      #Command Handler Module
      The Command Handler Module acts as the brain of JarvisAI. 
      It receives user input from either the chat interface or voice recognition module, analyzes the command, determines the appropriate action, and generates a response. 
        It handles tasks such as greetings, weather queries, system information, note-taking, calculations, web searches, application launching, and memory-based interactions.
          #Libraries 
          #Tkinter
          Used to develop graphical user interface.
          #SpeechRecognition
          Used to capture and process voice input.
          #Edge-TTS
          Used for generating speech output.
          #Pillow
          Used for image handling.
          #WebBrowser
          Used for opening websites and online resources.
          #PyInstaller
          Used to package the application into a standalone executable file.
